# RemoteControlServer (0.1.0-beta)

This is v0.1.0 of the RemoteControlServer â€” a LAN-discoverable Android remote control & streaming server for gaming and remote control use.

## Features (v0.1.0)
- Screen capture via MediaProjection (480p@30 default).
- Hardware H.264 encoding (MediaCodec) with dynamic bitrate API exposure.
- Microphone capture (raw PCM) streaming (future: AAC/Opus encode).
- Local network discovery via UDP broadcast.
- Simple pairing via 6-digit code and QR generation.
- AEAD protection using Google Tink for media frames (pairing-provisioned keyset).
- AccessibilityService-based multi-touch injection (true multi-pointer gestures).
- Telemetry (battery/thermal sampling).
- Control server listening on TCP port 5000 (JSON messages).

## Build
1. Android SDK + JDK 17 recommended.
2. `./gradlew clean assembleDebug`
3. Install `app/build/outputs/apk/debug/app-debug.apk`

## Notes & Future Work
- Add proper TLS WebSocket control channel (planned).
- Add secure key exchange (ECDH) instead of storing serialized keysets on-device.
- Add AAC/Opus audio encoding and playback support on client.
- Add WAN relay server for remote access.
- Integrate Crashlytics or Sentry.

## Privacy
- This app requests accessibility and screen capture permissions. It is intended only for devices you control. Do not share pairing codes with untrusted parties.